  "texts": [
    "For example, training is initially performed with 16-bit or 32-bit floating-point numbers, which are then converted to 8-bit, or 4-bit fixed-point numbers for fast & easy end-user execution.",
    "In this way, the model can work well even on mobile phones, personal computers, or Internet of Things (IoT) devices.",
    "An extreme form of this approach is when the weights are converted to 1-bit numbers.",
    "This can be a full binary conversion as the authors suggest, using the values {-1,0,1} (hence the 1.58 bits).",
    "One might think that such extreme discretization would render the neural network completely useless, but in fact, the opposite is true."
  ],
